The Great Northern Forest is a 400-square-mile continuous canopy between Midgaard (south) and Kowloon (north), the primary overland trade corridor between the two cities. Before either city existed, three peoples occupied the forest: the Everkeepers (druidic order tending ironpine groves, maintaining seven-pace planting-rings now buried throughout the Ironpine Rise), the Mire-Speakers (fenland inhabitants of the Mosswater Bends, whose medicinal and navigation knowledge Midgaard's quartermasters depended on), and the Cairn-Keepers (high-ridge megalith maintainers who practiced ancestor communion at standing stones, their burial tradition placing honored dead facing north toward the Cold Throne). The Lantern Road was built by quartermaster Ilren Voss using the Bent Mile Principle — roads yield to terrain rather than forcing straight lines through living forest. The Northern Covenant, signed at the Oath-Crossing glade, established joint governance: no army in war formation on the road, timbering restricted to safety cuts, shrine groves inviolable, both cities maintaining wardens without sole territorial claim. Dual-mark manifests (Midgaard wax plus Kowloon thread-knot) were added after a convoy massacre. Current factions: roadwardens and lamp-keepers (joint-commission, mixed city loyalty), mire-clans (Mire-Speaker descendants), stone-antler circles (Cairn-Keeper descendants), Ashfang warbands (exile coalition rejecting both cities), Rootbound cult remnants (forest-deity believers sabotaging road infrastructure). Thornwood estate-forest is carved out from normal warden jurisdiction due to necrotic contamination and an active crystal substrate whose binding is failing.

