Midgaard's relationship to the Great Northern Forest is primarily commercial and administrative. The Granite Arcade — Midgaard's northernmost civic spine point — serves as the administrative hub for all forest-related commerce, contracts, and ranger writs. Road wardens carry Midgaard guild chits and report to Granite Arcade offices. Lamp-keepers are paid from Midgaard's civic treasury through a budget line that has survived every political dispute for two centuries. Timber surveyors from the Woodwrights Guild conduct annual assessments of the southern verge, marking approved harvest trees with green chalk seal; unauthorized felling means tool confiscation and route ban. The road's eastern approaches carry ash-mortar paving from the Ash-and-Iron rebuild, connecting the forest road to the broader post-crisis infrastructure program. The Ashfall Monsoon ash winters blanketed the canopy, poisoned shallow streams, killed an estimated third of large game, and drove wolves into the southern verge for the first time in living memory — generating the first formal Passage Tithe system. The Reckoning faction's critique of the Granite Arcade trade ledger — specifically the entry "forty iron bars and six condemned debtors" transferred to "the mountain academy" — implicates Roc Road and by extension the northern forest route as part of a condemned-labor transfer corridor during the Continuity era.

