Rakuen has no direct route connection to the Great Northern Forest — the forest lies north of Midgaard while Rakuen lies south. The forest is relevant to Rakuen primarily as a factor in Midgaard's supply health: disruptions on the Lantern Road affect Midgaard's northern grain and timber inputs, which cascade into Midgaard's capacity to supply Rakuen through the Eccentric Woodland corridor. During the Ash Winters, the same Cinderteeth volcanic activity that disrupted Lantern Road traffic also disrupted the Eccentric Woodland approaches — Rakuen experienced both supply chains degrading simultaneously, without either Midgaard or Kowloon being able to prioritize Rakuen's needs over their own supply security.

